1
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,640
Where's Xu Xinglang?

2
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:12,880
Why isn't he here yet?

3
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:13,840
No idea.

4
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:14,840
Producer Li is calling him.

5
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:16,400
No idea where Li Fang has gone either.

6
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:21,360
Be quiet.

7
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:23,200
The director is in a bad mood right now.

8
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,320
Director Du.

9
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:26,840
The auspicious window is almost over.

10
00:01:27,039 --> 00:01:28,720
We have to start now or we'll miss the lucky hour.

11
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:29,680
Let’s not wait any longer.

12
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,920
He must have been held up by something.

13
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,600
Can't we even get a hold of his assistant?

14
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,280
We can reach his assistant.

15
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,600
He keeps saying he is almost here

16
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,000
"Almost" where? God only knows.

17
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:43,720
I’m done waiting.

18
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,640
Let's start the ceremony.

19
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:45,800
Alright.

20
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,280
Everyone.

21
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,000
Thank you all for taking your time.

22
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,960
to join us for the production opening ceremony of The Crossroad.

23
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,840
Now let's invite our crews.

24
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:55,400
to assist all our main cast

25
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,000
and crew members with the incense offering.

26
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:58,000
Is it okay to skip the lead?

27
00:01:58,479 --> 00:01:59,280
You're asking me?

28
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:00,800
Who should I ask, the god?

29
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,240
Let's welcome Director Du.

30
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,680
He's been drinking again.

31
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,240
How much did he drink?

32
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,640
Why are you leaving again

33
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,400
I never thought there would be.

34
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,000
any other kind of relationship between us.

35
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:51,360
I’m a assassin.

36
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,560
You're my client.

37
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:55,560
That's all.

38
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,320
Assassin.

39
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,160
Kill.

40
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,080
Cut!

41
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,720
Xu Xinglang!

42
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,840
What's going on?

43
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,640
Sorry, Director.

44
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,760
Let's do another take.

45
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,480
Start from your line.

46
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:15,520
Assassin.

47
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,600
Then did you finish the job?

48
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,240
As an assassin..

49
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,640
you took the client's money.

50
00:03:21,079 --> 00:03:22,079
you accepted the client's job.

51
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,480
Did you finish the job?

52
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,400
Answer me.

53
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,320
That's because

54
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,800
I didn't know you were trying to kill yourself.

55
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,360
Then kill me now.

56
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:34,880
Kill me.

57
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,400
Kill me.

58
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,560
Kill me.

59
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,120
Be careful

60
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:05,400
Mr.Jian, is Mr.Xu okay?

61
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:13,840
Are you okay?

62
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,079
I'm fine.

63
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:17,800
You're the one who has a problem.

64
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,160
Whatever happened last night.

65
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,360
once you're here on set.

66
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,560
and the camera starts rolling.

67
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,040
you give your best performance.

68
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,360
If you're so fond of slacking off.

69
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,440
why be an actor at all?

70
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:28,640
Mr.Jian.

71
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,240
Well said.

72
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:31,920
You're right.

73
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,480
Are you two okay?

74
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:35,920
We're fine.

75
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,120
Sorry, Director.

76
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,360
Sorry, everyone.

77
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:46,880
I promise.

78
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:48,960
this won't happen again.

79
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,440
What?

80
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,120
Reverting to your toxic self?

81
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,840
If you aren't being snarky, will you actually choke?

82
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,400
I'd go crazy.

83
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,800
Let me show you some fan-made CP edits of you two.

84
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,400
Look at these filters.

85
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,400
This BGM.

86
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:16,400
This caption.

87
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,040
You even have a ship name now.

88
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,640
"Jian-Xing Chronicles."

89
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:22,880
That sounds nice.

90
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,960
"Hearts for Mo."

91
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,520
That sounds nice too.

92
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,440
Am I making some kind of money

93
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,920
that I'm not aware of?

94
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,000
No, why would you ask that?

95
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,240
I thought you got rich recently.

96
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,760
Since you seem to have so much free time.

97
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,360
You brat, I wish.

98
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,040
I'm off to work.

99
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,480
Ugh, you're annoying.

100
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,360
Hey, Sleeping Beauty, wake up.

101
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,120
Check Weibo quickly.

102
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:40,840
I'm not lookin.

103
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:42,800
Please.

104
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,440
This better be something earth-shaking.

105
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,159
Although we haven't worked together for long.

106
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,840
Mr.Jian's professional skills

107
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:58,760
and his work ethic.

108
00:06:58,760 --> 00:06:59,840
have earned my deepest respect.

109
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,160
Also thank you, Teacher Jian.

110
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,960
Brave rescue on set today

111
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,560
I look forward to learning from him.

112
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,400
Is he out of his mind?

113
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,400
I told you.

114
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,600
Don't post anything, don't post anything.

115
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,880
Don't post anything!

116
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,000
Do you take my words as nonsense?

117
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:25,920
But I already posted it.

118
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,040
What can we do?

119
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,440
How about

120
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:30,720
you just delete it.

121
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:31,400
Well...

122
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,040
Wouldn't that just be a dead giveaway?

123
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,280
Exactly.

124
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,600
What's the point of yelling at me?

125
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:42,880
Just go get some sleep.

126
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,480
If you don't cause trouble for one day.

127
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:48,400
you're clearly not happy.

128
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,200
You can't sleep either.

129
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:04,760
Fine.

130
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,400
You get back to work.

131
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,320
I'm going out for some fresh air.

132
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:08,960
Xu Xinglang.

133
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:11,480
What's up?

134
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,440
Thank you.

135
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,160
Why did you choose to become a assasin?

136
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:44,760
Just making a living.

137
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:49,840
The money I have now.

138
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,320
is more than enough to support you for a lifetime.

139
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,520
It's not enough.

140
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,520
What exactly do you want?

141
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,800
Cut!

142
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,120
Good, that's a wrap.

143
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:06,000
Take a break, everyone. We’re switching sets.

144
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,360
Xiao Zhao.

145
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,400
Xinglang.

146
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,920
You've improved so much all of a sudden.

147
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,280
Did you finally get the hang of it?

148
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:20,560
Tell me.

149
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:22,680
Did Jian Mo give you private lessons?

150
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,400
Mr.Jian is truly professional.

151
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:27,520
Mr.Xu.

152
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,480
Your iced Americano, no sugar.

153
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,400
Mr.Jian, your latte.

154
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,600
You two are getting along really well.

155
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:35,840
Love ya.

156
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:37,440
Okay.

157
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:38,760
Keep it up.

158
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,360
Where's my cup of coffee?

159
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,960
Could we get a quick behind-the-scenes shot of you two?

160
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:48,760
Sure.

161
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:49,640
Let's do it.

162
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,720
What kind of shots do you want?

163
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,800
A couple shot or a solo one?

164
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,480
Just talk naturally to each other would be fine

165
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:54,800
Alright.

166
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,040
What should we talk about?

167
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:01,600
I don't know.

168
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,800
They're recording, why are you laughing?

169
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:08,880
Nothing.

170
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,640
Just messing with you.

171
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,040
Perfect, perfect

172
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:14,600
That was so natural.

173
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:16,320
You guys have such great chemistry!

174
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:37,680
What are you staring at?

175
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:38,840
Don't you recognize me anymore?

176
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,480
Honestly, I barely recognize you anymore.

177
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,200
I seem to remember.

178
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,560
you're not a method actor.

179
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,000
Why are you so full of genuine emotion today?

180
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,440
What nonsense are you talking about?

181
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,800
See? You're getting all defensive now.

182
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:55,920
Something is definitely up.

183
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:57,720
You just saw it wrong.

184
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,440
You definitely saw it wrong.

185
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,440
We're about to film.

186
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,000
Hold this for me.

187
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,400
Oh boy, oh boy.

188
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,720
There is definitely something going on.

189
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,560
Trouble is coming

190
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:25,800
I said I got it.

191
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,000
What's wrong with you?

192
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,480
Nothing's wrong.

193
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,440
No.

194
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,720
You're not acting like yourself.

195
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,960
What exactly happened?

196
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,440
Really nothing.

197
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,160
You're overthinking.

198
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:55,680
Mr.Jian

199
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,920
the script has been revised.

200
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,760
These are the new pages.

201
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,160
Thank you.

202
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:19,640
Xinglang.

203
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,080
They cut a huge chunk of your scenes.

204
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:22,840
Did you know about this?

205
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:27,640
I know.

206
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:29,520
And you just don't care?

207
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,080
I asked for them to be cut.

208
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,400
Xinglang has other events scheduled.

209
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,520
He doesn't have much time left on set.

210
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,200
We need the production team to cooperate.

211
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:47,520
Those scenes are very important.

212
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,600
for portraying the character.

213
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,240
If we cut them.

214
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,040
the entire character arc will change.

215
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,760
Jian Mo, right?

216
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:56,840
Diligence is a good trait.

217
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,480
But being too diligent

218
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,200
just makes you a nuisance.

219
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:02,920
Xinglang.

220
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,600
Let's wrap up today's scenes early.

221
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,800
We need to head to Chongqing

222
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:06,600
for a gala dinner

223
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:20,560
It's just work.

224
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:22,640
Why take it so seriously?

225
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:24,640
Besides.

226
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,440
I'm not even upset.

227
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,080
Why are you getting so worked up?

228
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:30,960
Work?

229
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:34,840
Didn't you say you wanted to transition

230
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:35,960
and become a good actor?

231
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,240
Is this your professional attitude?

232
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,520
Is this really just a "job" to you?

233
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,160
It's creation.

234
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,800
It's self-expression.

235
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,400
Mr.Jian.

236
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:48,880
That's how you see it.

237
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,080
Not me.

238
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:57,160
We'll fly back first thing tomorrow morning.

239
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,760
Honestly, you shouldn't blame him.

240
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:05,880
He doesn't have a choice.

241
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,880
His company has strict control over its artists.

242
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,920
Isn't he the company's cash cow?

243
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:13,120
Exactly.

244
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,760
Precisely because he's a cash cow.

245
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,320
they control him even more tightly.

246
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,760
Why make five grand when you can make ten?

247
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,760
You were a bit harsh back there.

248
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,200
Actually deep down, Xu Xinglang.

249
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,480
isn't happy about it either.

250
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,280
I'm not hungry.

251
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,280
I don't want to eat.

252
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,440
Why are you here?

253
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:52,920
How did you get in?

254
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:58,680
Used a key card, obviously.

255
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,560
The Godfather.

256
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,520
You like this movie too?

257
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:13,880
Whenever I feel like I can't keep being an actor.

258
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:14,880
and want to give up acting

259
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:17,680
I also love watching this movie.

260
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,160
Marlon Brando

261
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,360
stayed in obscurity for ten years.

262
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,760
He returned to the peak once again with The Godfather.

263
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,280
I think

264
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,480
maybe I can survive my own rock bottom.

265
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,440
and reach my own peak again.

266
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:39,600
Do you think

267
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,560
this is my peak?

268
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,440
A celebrity chasing trends,

269
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,440
a money-making tool for the company.

270
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,840
Is this my ultimate peak

271
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,400
I told you

272
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,840
I don't want to release a single.

273
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,640
I'm an actor,

274
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,000
not a singer.

275
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,520
Why did you sign me up for a music video

276
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,160
without my consent?

277
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:04,320
Besides,

278
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,320
why are my scenes being cut?

279
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,160
Xinglang,

280
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,440
this is the company's business strategy.

281
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:12,600
It's for the good of your career development.

282
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,680
You mean it’s good for the company's wallet.

283
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,720
How many "Alpha CEO" roles do you give me a year?

284
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,440
I'm sick of playing them.

285
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:20,800
I told you

286
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,760
I want to take on other types of roles.

287
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,200
Xinglang,

288
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,400
watch your tone.

289
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,200
An actor who only just tasted fame

290
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,400
can't afford to be this picky.

291
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,440
You won't last long in this industry that way.

292
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,120
I think the plan you've laid out for me

293
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,280
is what won't last.

294
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:38,760
Do you think career transition

295
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:39,880
is that easy?

296
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,120
Countless actors have failed to transition.

297
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,480
Their commercial value plummeted.

298
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:45,680
Do you have any idea

299
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,960
what a drop in a drama's ratings means to the company?

300
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,320
I'm willing to take the risk.

301
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:51,080
Enough!

302
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,080
Everything will proceed according to the contract.

303
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,640
Xinglang,

304
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,320
The agency has your best interests at heart.

305
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:02,560
Until you have enough leverage

306
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,200
don't try to go rogue.

307
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:06,319
There’s another "Alpha CEO" script.

308
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,200
The platform specifically requested you.

309
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,160
Just wrap this project up quickly

310
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,160
and move on to the next set.

311
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,640
I don't mind playing the CEO roles.

312
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:22,760
I just can't accept it.

313
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,960
I can't stand the thought

314
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,560
that my whole life

315
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:34,520
being held on such a tight leash.

316
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,520
This crushing sense of powerlessness.

317
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:39,200
hurts more than playing any number of repetitive roles.

318
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,120
Alright.

319
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,640
Let me take you somewhere.

320
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,000
Jian Mo.

321
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,320
Long time no see.

322
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,000
I've been focusing on filming lately,

323
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,240
and I brought a friend along for a visit.

324
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:04,640
Don't let us hold you up.

325
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,360
I'll help myself.

326
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,920
I knew you were the best.

327
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:07,800
Alright.

328
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,520
Take your time chatting.

329
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,680
It seems you come here often.

330
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,880
You look very familiar with this place.

331
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:18,560
When I had no roles to play,

332
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,640
I worked here as a resident singer.

333
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:23,960
I've acted in a few productions after all.

334
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:25,400
I'm not a good singer,

335
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:26,960
but I still had an audience.

336
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:28,360
I could make three or four hundred bucks

337
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:29,920
a night.

338
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,200
You won Best Actor before.

339
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,640
Even after what happened,

340
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,080
it shouldn't have come to this.

341
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,520
What's wrong with singing here?

342
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,600
I made many friends.

343
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,840
I met all kinds of people.

344
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,960
It really helped with my acting.

345
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:50,840
No wonder you're a Best Actor.

346
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:53,000
You think about acting all the time.

347
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,040
Cut it out.

348
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:55,280
Don't tease me.

349
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,400
I'm not teasing you.

350
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:59,080
I'm sincerely complimenting you.

351
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,360
Alright then.

352
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:01,920
I'll sing you a song.

353
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,040
So you know

354
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:04,200
I'm not only a Best Actor,

355
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,520
but also a 'Best Singer'.

356
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,480
Let's hear it.

357
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:19,760
This next song

358
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,240
is dedicated to my very good friend.

359
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:22,560
I hope you like it.
